{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/helping-helpers/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://helpinghelp.foundation"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d871adbe-a69e-57b4-85ea-2d78f36decdf","excerpt":"Why Helping helpers is more effective than trying to help an individual in-need.  When we help someone or a group of individuals, although the help is good, it…","html":"<p>Why Helping helpers is more effective than trying to help an individual in-need. </p>\n<p>When we help someone or a group of individuals, although the help is good, it may reach those only. And if the same help is provided to an individual or a organization, they can do much more.</p>\n<h2>A few</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>It’s easy to talk to someone who is aready doing kind work.</li>\n<li>Individuals or Organizations have reach to more people/regions/countries. And example can be helping <a href=\"https://www.redcross.org/\">RedCross</a> will help them to do more. They work in lots of regions/countries otherwise we cannot reach.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Kind of help NonProits will look for:</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Technology Assistance</li>\n<li>Fundrasing</li>\n<li>Marketing</li>\n<li>Professional Services</li>\n<li>Help with Management</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Some NonProfits (like us) that help other NonProfits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gatesfoundation.org/\">Gates Foundation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://taprootfoundation.org/\">TapRoot Foundation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.volunteermatch.org/\">Volunteer Match</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/helping-helpers/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Helping Helpers","date":"10 May, 2020","description":"The psychology of helping helpers and why it is more effective.","tags":["blog","learn","featured","focus"],"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/8d2d6adf064ff81f538ff64e956bf181/about.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='62'%20height='62'%20viewB